      • getErrors

        public Map<String,String> getErrors(String... path)
        Returns parsed map of errors (key = "code", value = "message").
        This is the util method that helps to parse json returned in the error body by specified path to the array of errors.
        For instance, to get all errors related to the customer email, getErrors("customer", "email") should be called.
        Parameters:
        path - of nested json fields to array of errors
        Returns:
        map of error codes and messages if found, null otherwise

      • getLineItemErrors

        public List<Map<String,String>> getLineItemErrors(String property)
        Returns the ordered list of line items errors for specific property. Index of errors corresponds to the index of line item in the checkout. Could contain null items that represents no errors for the particular line item.
        Parameters:
        property - filter for line item errors (e.g. "quantity")
        Returns:
        ordered list of line items errors
